node.text:
You're going to LOVE these Chicken Romano Meatballs made with Romano cheese, herbs, and garlic in a lemony white wine pan sauce. This recipe is from my friend @howsweeteats newest cookbook, Everyday Dinners: Real-Life Recipes to Set Your Family Up for a Week of Success. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

node.text:
One of my favorite summer date nights is dinner on our boat on the south shore of Long Island. The waterways, coves and islands give you so many perfect locations to anchor and enjoy the views. This salad takes advantage of gorgeous end of season tomatoes and basil, lightly pan-fried chicken cutlets and fresh mozzarella. It’s delicious, and enjoying it on our @searayboats means social distancing is never and issue and we can choose a different location every time we go! We are newbies to boating, but thanks to the joystick control on our Sea Ray boat, Tommy picked it up fast and looks like he’s been boating for years. Here’s the recipe, hope you enjoy as much as we did! 
 
Chicken Cutlet Caprese Salad
4 servings

For Chicken Cutlets

2 boneless, skinless chicken breasts (16 oz)
2 large eggs or egg whites, beaten
1/2 + 2 TBSP cup seasoned breadcrumbs 
3 tablespoons grated Parmesan cheese
kosher salt and fresh pepper
1 tablespoon butter
1 teaspoon olive oil

For the Platter

2 Heirloom tomatoes, diced
8 ounces fresh Bocconcini mozzarella halved
1/2 cup fresh basil leaves
6 cups mixed baby greens

Simple Balsamic dressing, combine equal parts balsamic and extra virgin olive oil.

For the chicken:

Cut chicken breasts in half horizontally so you end up with 4 thin pieces of chicken. Working with 1 piece of chicken at a time, pound chicken until 1/4-inch thick. Set aside and repeat with the remaining 3 pieces.

Season with 3/4 teaspoon salt and black pepper, to taste.

Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese in a medium bowl. In another bowl beat eggs.

Dip cutlets in egg, then breadcrumbs.

Heat a large nonstick skillet over medium heat. If cooking in two batches, add half of the butter and olive oil.
When butter melts, add the cutlets and cook about 4 to 6 minutes on each side, until golden brown and cooked through. Repeat.

For the Platter:

Slice the chicken cutlets.  Arrange the baby greens in the center of the platter. Place the chicken, tomatoes, mozzarella, basil all round. Cover tight with plastic and keep chilled.

462 calories/Fat: 24.0g/Carbs: 14.5g/Protein: 45.4g
9 blue points (without dressing)

node.text: Everyone loves Tommy’s home-fries! And yes, he uses canned diced potatoes which makes them quick and easy (trust me here!) He also likes to use a wok for maximum surface area to get those potatoes really browned. There’s no recipe, just a little olive oil, onion, drained potatoes, salt and adobo seasoning (or any seasoned salt). Enjoy! #breakfast #breakfastpotatoes #potatoes #homefries #glutenfree #yummy
